[1] Italy
Date: 12 Sep 2013
Source: IZSAM "Giuseppe Caporale" National reference centre, Italy: WND Epid bull No 5, 2013 [in Italian, machine trans. summarised, edited]
http://sorveglianza.izs.it/emergenze/west_nile/pdf/Bollettino%2012_09_2013.pdf


West Nile disease in Italy, 2013, Epidemiological bulletin No 5, surveillance in equidae
-----------------------------------------------
Monitoring is carried out in equidae by means of periodic examination of sentinel horses, spot checks of resident equidae, and verification of suspected cases of WND.

On 12 Sep 2013, the CESME (National Reference Centre for Exotic Diseases) confirmed 3 clinical outbreaks in the regions of Emilia Romagna and Lombardy. Phylogenetic analyzes carried out on samples of the organs of a horse knocked down made it possible to define the strain as WND-lineage II.

--
Communicated by:
Gert van der Hoek
Senior Moderator
FluTrackers.com

[IZSAM stands for Istituto Zooprofilattico Sperimentale dell'Abruzzo e del Molise "Giuseppe Caporale," the Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute (IZS) in Teramo, Italy. http://www.izs.it/IZS/Engine/RAServePG.php/P/250010010303/L/1. - Mod.AS]

