[3] Greece
Date: Mon 16 Sep 2013 [accessed]
Source: FAO/Empress website [scanned, summarised, edited]
http://empres-i.fao.org/eipws3g/#h=0


Six clinical WND cases in animals have been reported by Greece, observed between 8-30 Jul 2013, of which 5 cases were in horses (2 in Anatoloki Makedonia, and 3 in Dyitiki Ellada) and one in an unspecified mammal in Attiki).

--
Communicated by:
Gert van der Hoek
Senior Moderator
FluTrackers.com

[According to OIE's WAHID database, during 2012, the following European countries reported WND cases in equidae:

Croatia, July-November 2012, 11 cases;
Greece, July-September, 14 cases;
Spain (Andalucia), unspecified dates, 3 cases.

For further details, select disease, country and year at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Diseaseinformation/statusdetail.

Among mammals, disease occurs mainly in equids (horses, donkeys and mules). In WNV endemic regions, preventive vaccination of horses is recommended. For further reading on WNV in animals, please refer to http://www.cfsph.iastate.edu/Factsheets/pdfs/west_nile_fever.pdf. - Mod.AS]

[Given the number of human cases in various parts of Europe this transmission season [2013], it would be surprising if there were not a corresponding number of equine WNV cases as well. - Mod.TY

ProMED-mail HealthMaps can be accessed at the following URLs:
